<plot>The 1967 All-Star Game was tied 1-1 at the end of 14 innings. 'Tony Perez' (VI) homered off of 'Catfish Hunter' (qv) in the 15th inning, and the National League won when 'Tom Seaver' (qv) pitched a scoreless bottom of the inning, preserving the win for 'Don Drysdale' (qv).</plot><plot>The 1967 All-Star Game was tied 1-1 at the end of 14 innings. 'Tony Perez' (VI) homered off of 'Catfish Hunter' (qv) in the 15th inning, and the National League won when 'Tom Seaver' (qv) pitched a scoreless bottom of the inning, preserving the win for 'Don Drysdale' (qv).</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?002986</url></doc>
